  "prompt": "Can I use Google images in my website?",
  "response": "Using Google images directly on your website can lead to copyright infringement. Here are some guidelines:\n\n1. Do Not Simply Copy Images\n- Downloading and using images from Google search results without permission can be illegal\n- These images are likely copyrighted\n\n2. Legal Ways to Use Images:\n- Use images with Creative Commons licenses\n- Purchase stock images from sites like Shutterstock or Getty Images\n- Use royalty-free image websites like:\n  \u2022 Unsplash\n  \u2022 Pixabay\n  \u2022 Pexels\n  \u2022 Canva\n- Create your own images\n- Get permission from the original copyright holder\n\n3. Google Image Search Tools\n- Use Google Image search filter for usage rights\n- Select \"Tools\" > \"Usage Rights\" to find images labeled for reuse\n\n4. Proper Attribution\n- Even with free images, always check and follow attribution requirements\n- Some licenses require crediting the original creator\n\n5. Best Practices\n- Always verify image licensing\n- When in doubt, ask for permission\n- Consider hiring a designer or photographer\n\nRemember: Using copyrighted images without permission can result in legal action and financial penalties.",
